By now you are probably familiar with the term “quarantini” – a cocktail you drink alone at home.
For starters, learn to make a simple syrup.
If the result isn’t sweet enough, add a bit of simple syrup.
One ounce dark (not spiced) rum, one ounce white rum, 2.5 ounces pineapple juice, 1.25 ounces orange juice, and ¾ ounce coconut cream.
Two ounces white rum, two tablespoons jam, ¼ ounce simple syrup and ¾ ounce lime juice.